The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Briefs

 Seven passengers of Indian airlines Calcutta-Aizawl flight were offloaded on Sunday as the aircraft weight needed to be reduced because of bad weather at the Northeast destination. An Indian spokesperson said fuel and part of the passenger and cargo weight had to be reduced for the flights safety. Two of the seven passengers were later sent to Silchar on another flight. The others will take Mondays flight.

 SSKM Hospital and Calcutta Medical College and Hospital suffered power cuts on Sunday. Hospital sources said the cuts were due to a cable fault which occurred during maintenance work. 

 Ten shanties were gutted and three persons injured in a fire that broke out on SB Park Road, at Titagarh, on the northern fringes of the city, on Sunday morning. 

 Two youths on a motorcycle snatched a gold chain from the neck of Ashima Bhattacharya while she was walking along Russa Road Second Lane, in the Charu Market police station area, on Saturday afternoon. 




